               <head>Translation of Ibn Khallikan’s Vafayat &amp; a history of Sultan Jalal al-Din</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000556 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85014152 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068421">
                  <summary>Collection of works on early biography of the Islamicate Middle East and the conquest of Hindustan; some lacunae; later replacement leaves at beginning and end; provenance possibly connected with the Avadh Royal Library (see library annotations); IOL stamp: 7 Sep. 1907; transferred seal impressions; seal of Muḥammad Ṣanʿat Allāh Khān 1182; inscribed by Mirzā ʿAlī Khān Bahādur</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115517 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85054797" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3732-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="304v">ff. 1v-304v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled Persian translation of Ibn Khallikan’s influential biographical collection, the Vafayāt al-aʿyān va anbāʾ abnāʾ al-zamān, commissioned by the Ghaznavid ruler, Sultan Mahmud from Yūsuf ibn Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ibn ʿUs̲mān ibn ʿAlī ibn Aḥmad al-Shujāʿ al-Sanjarī, and completed in 250 fascicules or juzv (f. 304v)
</p>
                        <p>Two volumes bound together as one
</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7643">Yūsuf ibn Aḥmad</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7643">يوسف ابن احمد</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104967 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85072198" n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3732-item2">
                     <locus from="305r" to="636r">ff. 305r-636r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Unidentified universal history, extending from the rise of Islamic to the reign of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_53582598" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2006076497" role="pat">Sulṭān Jalāl al-Dīn</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Account ends abruptly without conclusion or colophon
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
